get.description: Execute simple queries over EnterpriseOne tables.

parameters.name: tableName
parameters.description: The name/id of the table in EnterpriseOne (for example F0101)

parameters.name: $token
parameters.description: The AIS token, use if you have already established a session.

parameters.name: $username
parameters.description: EnterpriseOne user ID, which is required if not using an established session.

parameters.name: $password
parameters.description: The EnterpriseOne user password, which is required if not using an established session.

parameters.name: $environment
parameters.description: EnterpriseOne environment, if not using a default environment.

parameters.name: $role
parameters.description: The EnterpriseOne role, if not using a default role.

parameters.name: $field
parameters.description: A list of fields to be returned in the response (for example F0101.AN8).

parameters.name: $filter
parameters.description:
A list of filters to be applied to fields. The format of each filter is: field name[space]operator[space]value (for example, F0101.AN8 EQ 6001 -- this would return the record with Address Number equal to 6001).
Release 9.2.8.3 and later, to use a special date value in the filter the format is: field name[space]operator[space]value[space]special date value (for example, F0101.UPMJ EQ 5 TODAY_MINUS_DAY -- this would return records with date values for five days ago).
Allowed operators: EQ, NE, STARTSWITH, ENDSWITH, CONTAINS, LT, LE, GT, GE.
Allowed special date values: TODAY, TODAY_PLUS_DAY, TODAY_MINUS_DAY, TODAY_PLUS_MONTH, TODAY_MINUS_MONTH, TODAY_PLUS_YEAR, TODAY_MINUS_YEAR

parameters.name: $filterType
parameters.description: Apply  MATCH_ALL or MATCH_ANY filter type to the list of filters.

parameters.name: $sort
parameters.description: List of sort orders for each field: - for descending, + for ascending (for example -F0101.AN8 or +F0101.AN8).

parameters.name: $limit
parameters.description: Maximum number of records to return.

parameters.name: $outputType
parameters.description: The output format type for data services.

parameters.name: $allowCache
parameters.description: Allow the response to be cached for faster subsequent fetches

returnControlIDs.description:
The returnControlIDs string is bar delimited, without a starting or ending bar. Form fields are just a single value. Grid fields are indicated with a grid id, followed by a bracketed list of grid columns. Subform fields are indicated with subform id underscore field id. For example: 33|34|17[24,26,28]|50_45|50_53|50_9[35,39,41].
Data request fields have two possible formats. There are no form fields so brackets ([]) are not used. For tables use only the field alias (AN8|ALPH). For business views, use table.alias (F4101.ITM|F4101.DSC1).
Release 9.2.8.3 and later, business views with the same table multiple times use table-instance.alias, you do not need to include instance for the first table (zero) only for instance of 1 or more (F4101.ITM|F4101-1.ITM).
